to those of people who exercised consistently throughout their lives. This was a  ___ of 32to 35ompared to people who did not exercise. Those who began exercising in middle age also saw reductions in their incidence of  ___ diseases,such as heart disease and cancer, which were similar to the steady exercisers.\\n      So why bother exercising consistently throughout your life? The authors of the study  ___ that some might interpret the study's findings to mean that they can delay starting an exercise program but this would be a mistake. There are other benefits, both mental and physical, to staying consistently active that we should not  ___ . These real health benefits include better  ___ functioning and lowered risk of gaining weight. The latter is  ___ important given the global obesity epidemic. In addition, experts assert that starting younger is better because,if you make a habit of exercising when you are young, you are more likely to keep up those  ___ later in life. It is ideal, then,for people to start exercising when they are children or  ___ ,and it is good to maintain an active lifestyle at all times regardless of your age. However,this study does indicate that, if you have not been active,you can still benefit if you start becoming active in your 40s and 50s", "wordBank": ["a", "b", "c", "d", "e", "f", "g", "h", "i", "j"], "partLabel": "Part Ⅲ", "partTitle": "Reading Comprehension", "questions": [{"id": "mqal5k9hsu7vb7", "score": 3.55, "answer": "a", "options": []}, {"id": "mqal7p1nw3i68w", "score": 3.55, "answer": "b", "options": []}, {"id": "mqal8kyanbu73s", "score": 3.55, "answer": "c", "options": []}, {"id": "mqal8onbdffzl5", "score": 3.55, "answer": "d", "options": []}, {"id": "mqal8rxc13ytcy", "score": 3.55, "answer": "e", "options": []}, {"id": "mqal8uwhcq3nvq", "score": 3.55, "answer": "f", "options": []}, {"id": "mqal8xlmc4nyhu", "score": 3.55, "answer": "g", "options": []}, {"id": "mqal942uds0ho0", "score": 3.55, "answer": "h", "options": []}